data.title: ZAMAN First Name Statistics by MyNameStats.com
data.meta_description: How popular is the first name ZAMAN? What is its origin and ethnicity? In which state is it most common? Find these facts and more in the statistics, charts and maps from MyNameStats.com
data.text:
Summary

The race and Hispanic origin distribution of the people with the name ZAMAN is 25.2% White, 3.8% Hispanic origin, 11.3% Black, 45.7% Asian or Pacific Islander, 13.7% Two or More Races, and 0.3% American Indian or Alaskan Native. These figures should be considered only as a rough estimate. The purpose of this graph is to compare the name's specific race and Hispanic origin distribution to the distribution in the general population of the US.

The vertical blue bars represent the race distribution of people that have the name. The yellow horizontal lines represent the race distribution of the general population. The amount by which the blue bars extend past the yellow horizontal lines determines how likely a person with the name will be part of a given race or Hispanic origin group.

On this basis, the people with the name ZAMAN have a higher likelyhood of being Two or More Races and a lower likelyhood of being White.

Summary

Shown are the top 20 most likely full names that have ZAMAN as a first name. The length of the bars represents an estimate of the the number of people with the name expressed as a percentage of all the people named ZAMAN.

The most popular full name is ZAMAN Khan. 9.91% of all the people named ZAMAN have this family name.

There are 70 last names associated with this first name.
